Mills was born in Laurel, Mississippi. She began playing golf at age 11 and her instructor was Johnny Revolta, an 18-time PGA Tour winner and PGA Championship victor. She won the Mississippi State Amateur eight consecutive years starting in 1954, and won the Gulf Coast Amateur twice. She was also medalist in the U.S. Junior, Western Junior, and the National Collegiate Championship. She attended Millsaps College where she was the No. 1 golfer - on the men's team - all four years. 